# Domain & Data Layer

## Domain Purity

`packages/domain/` — **zero imports** from NestJS, Prisma, HTTP, Redis

```typescript
// ✅ domain entity method
markAsPaid(confirmedBy: StaffId, at: DateTime): void {
  if (this.status === 'paid') throw new DomainError('ALREADY_PAID');
  this.status = 'paid';
  this.raise(new PaymentConfirmedEvent(this.id));
}
```

## Money

```typescript
amountRial: bigint   // ✅ DB, domain, internal API
amount: number       // ❌ NEVER for money
```

Display Toman in UI only — divide by `10n`

## Dates

- Store: `timestamptz` UTC
- Business: `Asia/Tehran`
- Overdue: Tehran date boundary — not UTC midnight mistake

## State Transitions

Before changing status → read `docs/03-modules/installments/state-machines.md`  
Transitions **only** in entity methods — not in use case if/else chains scattered

## Prisma / Migrations

- `prisma migrate dev` (local) · `migrate deploy` (prod)
- ❌ `db push` in staging/production
- Table names: `snake_case` plural
- Financial columns: `BIGINT` for rial
- Branch-scoped business rows: `branch_id NOT NULL` + `@@index([tenantId, branchId])` (ADR-015)
- Staff: `assigned_branch_ids[]` + optional `primary_branch_id` — not single `branch_id` FK

## Deletes (ADR-013 — mandatory)

Read: `docs/09-development/SOFT-DELETE-POLICY.md`

- **ALL business entities:** soft delete (`deletedAt`, `deletedById`)
- `prisma.*.delete()` — **FORBIDDEN** on business models
- Default reads: `deletedAt: null` via Prisma extension
- Installment `paid` / `waived`: **no delete** — status terminal only
- Customer privacy: soft delete + pseudonymize — not SQL DELETE
- AuditLog / OutboxEvent: append-only — never deleted

## Payment Flow (ADR-008)

Customer report → `PaymentAttempt.pending` → staff confirm → `Installment.paid`  
Never auto-paid on customer report (unless explicit setting + documented)

